OL,3,CThousands of residents affected as
OL,4,Ccordon around unexploded WW2 bomb
OL,5,Cextended
OL,7,FMore people are expected to be
OL,8,Faffected after the cordon area was
OL,9,Fextended from 200m to 300m on Thursday
OL,10,F22 February.
OL,12,FPlymouth City Council says the cordon
OL,13,Fis expected to be in place for at
OL,14,Fleast 36 hours.
OL,16,FResidents were offered shelter at the
OL,17,Fnearby North Prospect Library and in
OL,18,Flocal community centres, and have been
OL,19,Fadvised to stay with friends or family
OL,20,Fnearby until further notice but not
OL,21,Feverybody has moved.
